-- ICE Halts N.Y. Cotton-Options Trading, Will Expand Price Limit to 6 Cents
-- B y   S t e v e   S t r o t h
-- 2010-10-25T18:44:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/ice-halts-n-y-cotton-options-trading-will-expand-price-limit-to-6-cents.html
ICE Futures U.S. said in a  statement 
on its website that it halted trading in cotton-options
contracts after prices surged today by the daily limit to a
record. The 5-cent limit will be expanded to 6 cents a pound
tomorrow, ICE said in a separate  statement .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net  